28. Divide employees into two lists  based on marks i.e marks >80 and <80 in a single stream? 
Solution 1 :  Map<Boolean, List<Employee>> result =
                list.stream()
                    .collect(Collectors.partitioningBy(e -> e.getMarks() > 80));

        List<Employee> greaterThan80 = result.get(true);
        List<Employee> lessThanOrEqual80 = result.get(false);
Explianation : 
partitioningBy() → splits into 2 groups
mapping() → extracts only names
.values() → gives Collection<List<String>>
new ArrayList<>(...) → converts into List<List<String>>

Solution 2: 
Map<Boolean, List<String>> map = employees.stream().collect(Collectors.partitioningBy(e -> e.getMarks() >= 80,
                        Collectors.mapping(Employee::getName, Collectors.toList())));
 List<List<String>> listOfLists = Arrays.asList(map.get(true), map.get(false));

